  <section id="support-transformation" class="py-6">
    <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Support Org Transformation</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-3 text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2">
        <li>Rebuilt the tiered support structure (Tier 1–3) so there's clear ownership at each level and tickets don't stall.</li>
        <li>Designed and implemented a case age segmentation model (triage, midrange, long-tail) to improve prioritization and reduce backlog aging.</li>
        <li>Formalized Tier 3 (TSS-E) responsibilities and started cross-training the team on Zabbix monitoring, deployments, and system health. The goal was to get support working more like SRE.</li>
        <li>Made Root Cause Analysis (RCA) part of the Definition of Done, which meant Support, QA, and Engineering had to actually work together on fixes.</li>
        <li>Presented to the VP of Support on what was broken, what was working, and where we were headed.</li>
      </ul>
